               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">The tradition remembers that the church was "renovated" in the time of däğğazmač <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10102Webeha">Wǝbe Ḫayla Māryām</persName> and Metropolitan <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8388SalamaI">Salāmā</persName> (in tenure <date>1841-1867</date>); 
                     however, it states that the church was founded before that time, probably by the local community.</desc>
                  
                  
                  <ab type="tabot">
                     <measure quantity="10" cert="low"/>
                     Tābots (ca. 10?): some of them are three (two wooden and one marble) of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</persName>, two (one wooden and one marble) of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</persName>, 
                     <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName> , <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10775Trinity">Trinity</persName>.
                  </ab>
